verbose_text: Z. lotus fruit contains substantial amounts of glutamic acid, mineral matter, sterols, vitamins, tocopherols, fibers, amino acids, triacylglycerol, fatty acid, carbohydrate, and antioxidant compounds (phenols, flavonoids, etc.) which have been supposed to be responsible for most of its health benefits such as hypoglycemic, gastroprotective, immunomodulatory, and antioxidant properties [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
